sdrdaemon (3.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Removed sdrdaemon from the build and liblz4 dependency
  * Removed gr-sdrdaemonfec  GNUradio OOT module
  * Created a gr-sdrdaemon GNUradio OOT module with sdrdaemonsource block for Rx
  * RTLSDR: use asynchronous reads. Fixes I/Q stream issues in particular with RPi hosts

 -- Edouard Griffiths, F4EXB <f4exb06@gmail.com>  Sun, 25 Jun 2017 23:14:18 +0200

sdrdaemon (3.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fixed UDP transmission irregularities in Rx mode by adding buffering
  * Fixed bandwidth selection with the HackRF
  * Added file and documentation for service implementation in openSUSE

 -- Edouard Griffiths, F4EXB <f4exb06@gmail.com>  Sun, 18 Jun 2017 09:14:18 +0200

sdrdaemon (3.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Transmission support with HackRF
  * Also file sink for debugging
  * Renamed sdrdaemonfec to sdrdaemonrx

 -- Edouard Griffiths, F4EXB <f4exb06@gmail.com>  Sun, 11 Jun 2017 05:14:18 +0100

sdrdaemon (2.1.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fixed errors in cmake when no cm256cc package is available
  * Fixed cmake file to have a library suffix
  * Fixed wrong usage of assert: not working for release builds
    
